OL,5, Rising inflation led to government     
OL,6, interest payments hitting a record high
OL,7, for the month of January, figures show.
OL,9,FInterest payments hit #6.1bn last      
OL,10,Fmonth, the highest amount for a January
OL,11,Fsince records began in April 1997 and  
OL,12,Fup from #4.5bn last year.              
OL,14,FThe payments are pegged to the Retail  
OL,15,FPrices Index (RPI) measure of inflation
OL,16,F- which reached 7.8% in January.       
OL,18,FJanuary's interest payments were,      
OL,19,Fhowever, below the all-time high of    
OL,20,F#9bn in June last year.                
